  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Measuring the Impact of Gender-Based Violence Programmes in Emergencies: Taking a Local Perspective</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will address challenges faced by GBV-teams using complex data collection tools and methodologies in local contexts by creating space for reflection and learning on what would more successfully support local GBV partners to utilise data to improve GBV programming. Together participants will analyse existing data and identify innovative, yet simple new approaches to measure the impact of GBV programming more effectively. IRC will bring partners and new private sector collaborators together to ensure &#x201C;out of the box thinking and brainstorming&#x201D; and will also include a focus on new technology and media to support GBV result data collection, analysis and use for decision making. The workshop and learning spaces will be deliberately bilingual to allow French speaking teams in Burundi and DRC and English speaking teams in Tanzania to share learning and idea for innovative solutions.</narrative>
  </description>
